description:
When trying to execute an INSERT or INSERT DATA SPARQL 1.1 Update operation in Virtuoso using a graph pattern that contains a literal typed as xsd:duration, Virtuoso throws the following error:
Virtuoso 22023 Error SR553: Literal of type xsd:duration can not be created from SQL value of type INTEGER (189): SR066: Unsupported case in CONVERT (INTEGER -> UNK_DV_TYPE)

Minimal SPARQL 1.1 Update operation to reproduce the issue:
PREFIX ex: <http://example.com/>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

INSERT DATA {
  GRAPH ex:dataset {
    ex:A ex:duration "P1M"^^xsd:duration .
  }
}

Tested on Virtuoso 07.10.3211 (9d12959).
Related email thread.
